    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-28T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-28T05:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/576: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-28T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 28, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 28—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1330. Embassy’s 1319, August 27, 4 p.m., paragraph 3. The Foreign Office today
                    informed us “off the record” that on August 26 the Soviet Foreign Commissar
                    stated to the Japanese Ambassador in reply to representations by the latter with
                    regard to Soviet purchases of American gasoline and other military supplies that
                    the areas from which Japan obtains military supplies is not a matter with which
                    the Soviet Union is concerned and that correspondingly the Soviet Union cannot
                    admit that purchase by the Soviet Union of military supplies from the United
                    States is a matter of concern to Japan.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
